text:
let me list why one star:
- they won’t let anyone use the terrace if you are not eating and only drinking.
- i had the most horrendous pizza for €13.50, i had better dr. oetker ones

fantastic tapas bar in gràcia. the menu consists of traditional spanish food with a modern twist. all the dishes we had were outstanding:
—salmon marinated in a sake-soy sauce, served with avocado and lemongrass mayonnaise;
—eggplant with honey-lemon foam;
—cannelloni filled with spinach, raisins and nuts.
the deconstructed lemon pie is a great choice for dessert. the service is super friendly, and the atmosphere the perfect mix of busy and cozy. overall, la xula is by far better than a 4.2.
